le to a term of imprisonment of two (2) years to five (5) years. \n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Senegal}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Seychelles}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Somalia}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|South Africa}}\n| {{yes|Legal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Art. 525.-Instigating or Aiding another to commit Suicide.\n|(1) Whosoever, for any selfish or any base motive, instigates another to commit suicide, or aids and abets him to do so, is punishable with simple imprisonment of where the suicide is attempted bot not consumated, and with simple imprisonment from one to five years where it is accomplished.\n(2) Where the person who has committed suicide is partially or completely irresponsible, or had not attained the age of 18 years, the punishment is rigorous imprisonment not exceeding ten years.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://hrlibrary.umn.edu/research/Penal%20Code%20(English).pdf |publisher=Government of South Africa |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 525</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|South Sudan}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 213. Abetment of Suicide.\n|Subject to the provisions of section 214 of this Act, whoever abets any person to commit suicide, commits the offence of abetment of suicide, and upon conviction, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years or with a fine or with both.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 214. Abetment of Suicide by an Child or an Insane Person.\n|Whoever, abets any person under eighteen years of age, any insane person, delirious person, an idiot or any person in a state of intoxication, to commit suicide, commits an offence, and upon conviction, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for life or with a fine or with both.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 215. Attempt to Commit Suicide.\n|Whoever, attempts to or engages in any act towards committing suicide, commits an offence, and upon conviction, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year orwith a fine or with both.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wipo.int/edocs/lexdocs/laws/en/ss/ss014en.pdf |publisher=Government of Southern Sudan |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 213, 214 and 215.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Sudan}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{hidden\n|Article 213. Abetment of suicide.\n|Subject to the provisions of section 214 of this Act, whoever abets any person to commit suicide, commits the offence of abetment of suicide, and upon conviction, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years or with a fine or with both.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 215. Attempt to Commit Suicide.\n|Whoever, attempts to or engages in any act towards committing suicide, commits an offence, and upon conviction, shall be sentenced to imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year or with a fine or with both.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Swaziland}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Tanzania}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 216. Aiding suicide\n|Any person who\u2014\n:(1) procures another to kill himself; or\n:(2) counsels another to kill himself and thereby induces him to do\nso; or\n:(3) aids another in killing himself,\nis guilty of a felony, and is liable to imprisonment for life.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 217. Attempting suicide.\n|Any person who attempts to kill himself is guilty a misdemeanour.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.un.org/depts/los/LEGISLATIONANDTREATIES/PDFFILES/TZA_penal_code.pdf |publisher=Government of Tanzania |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 216 and 217.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Togo}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Tunisia}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Uganda}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 195. Suicide pacts.\n|It shall be manslaughter and shall not be murder for a person acting in pursuance of a suicide pact between him or her and another to kill the other or be a party to the other killing himself or herself or being killed by a third person.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 209. Aiding suicide.\n|Any person who\u2014<br/>\nprocures another to kill himself or herself;<br/>\ncounsels another to kill himself or herself and thereby induces him or her to do so; or\n(c) aids another in killing himself or herself,\ncommits a felony and is liable to imprisonment for life.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n{{hidden\n|Article 210. Attempting suicide.\n|Any person who attempts to kill himself or herself commits a misdemeanour.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icla.up.ac.za/images/un/use-of-force/africa/Uganda/Penal%20Code%20Act%20Uganda%201950.pdf |publisher=Government of Uganda |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 195, 209 and 210.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Western Sahara}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Zambia}}\n| {{yes|Legal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 200. Murder\n|Any person who of malice aforethought causes the death of another person by an unlawful act or omission is guilty of murder.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.gov.zm/sites/default/files/documents/acts/Penal%20Code%20Act.pdf |publisher=Government of Zambia |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 200.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Zimbabwe}}\n| {{yes|Legal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 50. Inciting or assisting suicide\n|Any person who incites, induces, aids, counsels, procures or provides the means for the suicide or attempted suicide of another person, knowing that the other person intends to commit suicide or realising that there is a real risk or possibility that the other person may commit suicide, shall be guilty of inciting or assisting suicide and liable to a fine up to or exceeding level fourteen, or imprisonment for life or any shorter period, or both such fine and such imprisonment.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.unodc.org/res/cld/document/zwe/2006/criminal_law_codification_and_reform_act_html/criminal_law_codification_and_reform_act.pdf |publisher=Government of Zimbabwe |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 50.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Americas===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:20%;\"|Country/region\n! colspan=3 style=\"width:25%;\"|[[De jure]]\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:25%;\"|Penalty\n! rowspan=2 style=\"width:30%;\"|Notes\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Suicide\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Physician-assisted suicide\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Voluntary euthanasia\n|-\n|''{{flag|Anguilla}}''\n| {{yes|Legal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Article 158. Abetment of suicide \n|(1) Any person who aids, abets, counsels or procures the suicide of another, or the attempt by another 