mmit suicide had not attained the age of majority, or had no capacity because of mental illness or senility, the punishment to be imposed upon the instigator or assistant shall be rigorous imprisonment not exceeding five years, where the suicide is attempted, and rigorous imprisonment not exceeding ten years, where it is consummated.\n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Gabon}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Gambia}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wipo.int/edocs/lexdocs/laws/en/mu/mu008en.pdf |publisher=Government of Gambia |title=Penal Code <sup>Article 206</sup>}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Ghana}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|Section 57\u2014Abetment of Suicide. Attempted Suicide.\n|(1) Whoever abets the commission of suicide by any person shall whether or not the suicide be actually committed, be guilty of first degree felony. \n(2) Whoever attempts to commit suicide shall be guilty of a misdemeanour. \n|headerstyle=background:#ccccff\n|style=text-align:center;\n}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wipo.int/edocs/lexdocs/laws/en/ss/ss014en.pdf |publisher=Government of Southern Sudan |title=Penal Code <sup>Section 57\u2014Abetment of Suicide. Attempted Suicide.</sup> |accessdate=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Guinea-Bissau}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n| {{unknown}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Kenya}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n| {{no|Illegal}}\n|\n{{hidden\n|209. Suicide pacts\n|(1) It shall be manslaughter, and shall not be murder, for a person acting in pursuance of a suicide pact between him and another to kill the other or be a party to the other killing himself or being killed by a third person.\n(2) Where it is shown that a person charged with the murder of another killed the other or was a party to his killing himself or being killed, it shal